- * AH, AH, AH-AH, OH

23:38.918 --> 23:40.787
- SANDY, SANDY,
SANDY, SANDY, OHH.

23:40.820 --> 23:42.755
- LOOK, TAD, IT'S OVER.

23:42.789 --> 23:44.023
KENDALL AND I ARE IN LOVE,

23:44.056 --> 23:46.225
AND WE'RE GONNA MAKE
A LIFE TOGETHER.

23:46.258 --> 23:47.627
- NOT A TRUE THING.

23:47.660 --> 23:50.162
- IT'S TIME FOR TAD TO GET BAD.

23:50.196 --> 23:51.631
- WHOA, WHOA, WHOA, WHOA, WHOA.

23:51.664 --> 23:53.700
- HOLD ON.
HOLD ON, GANG.

23:53.733 --> 23:55.702
YOU'VE GOT TO SETTLE THIS
LIKE MEN...

23:55.735 --> 23:58.638
WITH A SURF CONTEST
OR A DANCE-OFF.

24:01.608 --> 24:04.744
NO?
[together] NO.

24:04.777 --> 24:08.581
- THIS ISN'T OVER,
HOLLYWOOD.

24:08.615 --> 24:11.584
[engines revving]

24:14.921 --> 24:16.155
- OH, KENDALL,

24:16.188 --> 24:19.125
YOU WERE SO BRAVE
THE WAY YOU FOUGHT FOR ME.

24:19.158 --> 24:22.529
- HEY, UM, IF YOU NEED US,
WE'LL BE UP ON THE BLUFF.

24:22.562 --> 24:25.998
- WE'RE ONLY 800 PACES AWAY
FROM FINDING OUR TREASURE.

24:26.032 --> 24:27.600
- WHOO.
- NO, DON'T GO.

24:27.634 --> 24:29.001
DON'T GO.
DON'T GO.

24:29.035 --> 24:33.640
- AND IF YOU NEED ME,
I'LL BE IN LOVE WITH A MERMAID.

24:33.673 --> 24:35.141
- JAMES,
PLEASE DON'T GO.

24:35.174 --> 24:36.543
JAMES, JAMES, HELP, PLEASE.

24:36.576 --> 24:39.045
HELP, HELP, HELP.

24:39.078 --> 24:43.215
[together]
798, 799...

24:43.249 --> 24:46.953
800.

24:46.986 --> 24:48.220
- WHOO!

24:48.254 --> 24:49.288
WE'RE RICH, BOYS.

24:49.321 --> 24:53.993
PATCHY'S TREASURE
IS A MILLION-DOLLAR BEACH HOUSE.

24:54.026 --> 24:56.896
- PATCHY,
THIS HOUSE ISN'T YOUR TREASURE.

24:56.929 --> 24:58.698
THIS HOUSE WAS BUILT ON TOP
OF THE TREASURE.

24:58.731 --> 25:01.968
- OHH, WELL, THEN,
LET'S START DIGGING, BOYS.

25:02.001 --> 25:03.603
- NO, NO.
ARE YOU NUTS?

25:03.636 --> 25:05.938
WE CAN'T SMASH THROUGH
GRIFFIN'S MILLION-DOLLAR HOUSE.

25:05.972 --> 25:08.575
WE HAVE TO START DIGGING
IN THE BASEMENT

25:08.608 --> 25:09.642
BELOW THIS THIS VERY SPOT.

25:09.676 --> 25:11.010
- PERFECT.

25:11.043 --> 25:13.112
- GRIFFIN WILL NEVER NOTICE
IF WE'RE DIGGING AROUND

25:13.145 --> 25:14.747
IN HIS DUSTY,
OLD BASEMENT.

25:14.781 --> 25:16.949
- HOO-HOO!
- YES.

25:16.983 --> 25:18.718
- UNLESS, OF COURSE,
IT'S FILLED

25:18.751 --> 25:21.654
WITH THIS PRICELESS
MING VASE COLLECTION.

25:24.991 --> 25:26.926
DON'T TOUCH THAT.

25:26.959 --> 25:29.696
- MARVIN, WHY AREN'T
THE BLACK EYED PEAS AVAILABLE?

25:29.729 --> 25:31.330
I NEED A BAND TO MAKE
THE PARTY SUCCESSFUL,

25:31.363 --> 25:34.033
AND I'M STILL WAITING
ON MY CHAIRS

25:34.066 --> 25:36.636
AND MY ICE SCULPTURE,

25:36.669 --> 25:39.205
AND MY CENTERPIECE.

25:39.238 --> 25:41.908
I DON'T KNOW YOU.

25:41.941 --> 25:44.811
IS THAT A JELLYBEAN LIKENESS
OF MY HEAD?

25:44.844 --> 25:47.146
- A CENTERPIECE THAT YOU
AND YOU PARTY GUESTS

25:47.179 --> 25:51.951
WILL NEVER FORGET.

25:51.984 --> 25:55.755
- LISTEN, KATIE,
YOU'RE VERY SWEET,

25:55.788 --> 25:58.357
BUT I CAN'T HAVE A LITTLE, TINY,
SWEET TEN-YEAR-OLD

25:58.390 --> 26:00.627
AS MY MANAGER,
CAN I?

26:00.660 --> 26:02.328
- WHY NOT?
- WHOA.

26:02.361 --> 26:03.730
- SEE,
I CAN BE AGGRESSIVE.

26:03.763 --> 26:05.364
- YES, THAT WAS DAUNTING.

26:05.397 --> 26:08.601
- HEY, RUSSELL,
THE SCRIPTS JUST ARRIVED.

26:08.635 --> 26:11.704
- UM, RIGHT,
I'M ACTUALLY IN THE MIDDLE

26:11.738 --> 26:13.606
OF ORGANIZING A SHINDIG.

26:13.640 --> 26:17.610
JUST SAY I'LL DO ANYTHING
BEGINNING WITH THE LETTER N

26:17.644 --> 26:20.346
AND ANYTHING WHERE I HAVE
A MONKEY SIDEKICK.

26:20.379 --> 26:23.382
- TELL YOU WHAT,
LET ME EYEBALL THESE FOR YOU,

26:23.415 --> 26:27.920
AND I WILL GET BACK TO YOU
WITH FULL COVERAGE.

26:27.954 --> 26:29.155
- THANK YOU.

26:29.188 --> 26:32.091
YOU CAN'T BE MY MANAGER.
YOU'RE TOO SMALL.

26:36.395 --> 26:38.130
- I DON'T CARE
IF SHE'S A MERMAID.

26:38.164 --> 26:42.234
SHE'S SWEET, SHE'S GOT FEET,
AND I'M FALLING FOR HER.

26:42.268 --> 26:43.202
- HI.

26:43.235 --> 26:48.174
- THEN I THINK YOU SHOULD GO
AND BE WITH HER.

26:48.207 --> 26:50.643
- OH, THERE YOU ARE.

26:50.677 --> 26:51.911
- HEY.
- HI.

26:51.944 --> 26:54.046
SHOULD I BE JEALOUS OF THAT GIRL
YOU WERE WITH?

26:54.080 --> 26:56.916
- NO,
SHE'S JUST A FRIEND.

26:56.949 --> 27:00.653
- GOOD,
'CAUSE I WAS KIND OF HOPING

27:00.687 --> 27:03.322
WE COULD BE MORE THAN FRIENDS.

27:03.355 --> 27:05.191
- PTHEW!

27:05.224 --> 27:08.194
- HEY. WOW.
YOU GUYS LOOK CUTE TOGETHER.

27:08.227 --> 27:10.429
I NEED TO TALK TO JAMES.

27:10.462 --> 27:13.766
- WAIT, NO, NO, SORRY.

27:13.800 --> 27:17.036
UH, YEAH, I WAS JUST ABOUT
TO MAKE OUT THERE, HUH?

27:17.069 --> 27:19.238
- I JUST REMEMBERED THE END
OF MERTEENS 4.

27:19.271 --> 27:24.043
IF YOU KISS A MERMAID,
YOU TURN INTO A MERMAN.

27:24.076 --> 27:26.212
- HEY.
- AHH!

27:26.245 --> 27:28.014
- MY DAD JUST CALLED,

27:28.047 --> 27:30.082
AND HE NEEDS MY HELP
AT THE OCEAN FLOOR,

27:30.116 --> 27:33.720
SO MAYBE I'LL SEE YOU LATER.

27:33.753 --> 27:35.054
- GREAT.

27:35.087 --> 27:36.923
YEAH,
THAT WOULD BE AWESOME.

27:36.956 --> 27:39.058
LET'S MEET UP LATER.

27:39.091 --> 27:41.327
- BYE.

27:41.360 --> 27:42.729
- WHAT DO I DO?
I THINK I'M IN LOVE.

27:42.762 --> 27:46.432
[upbeat guitar surfer music]

27:46.465 --> 27:48.067
- NOT NOW, DANCING TEENS.

27:48.100 --> 27:52.271
[together]
AWW.

27:52.304 --> 27:53.740
- WAS THE X REALLY NECESSARY?

27:53.773 --> 27:57.276
- HEY, COME ON,
THAT LOOKS COOL.

27:57.309 --> 27:59.712
- WAIT, SO WHAT'S THE BIG DEAL,
ANYWAYS?

27:59.746 --> 28:01.347
THESE THINGS ARE SUPER UGLY.
- DUDE.

28:01.380 --> 28:03.415
WOULD YOU STOP DOING THAT?

28:03.449 --> 28:06.753
THOSE ARE THOUSANDS
OF YEARS OLD AND PRICELESS.

28:06.786 --> 28:08.420
GRIFFIN TOLD US
NOT TO BE IN HERE.

28:08.454 --> 28:10.056
- OH, WHO CARES?

28:10.089 --> 28:11.357
BURIED UNDER THIS FLOOR

28:11.390 --> 28:13.760
ARE RICHES BEYOND
OUR WILDEST DREAMS,

28:13.793 --> 28:16.262
AND IF WE BREAK A VASE,
WE'LL BUY HIM A NEW ONE.

28:16.295 --> 28:18.030
- YEAH, HE'S RIGHT, LOGAN.

28:18.064 --> 28:20.366
- WHERE'D YOU GET
THE JACKHAMMER?

28:20.399 --> 28:23.002
- JACKHAMMER STORE.

28:23.035 --> 28:25.404
- THANK YOU.

28:25.437 --> 28:27.807
- YOU'RE SURE YOU KNOW HOW
TO WORK ONE OF THESE THINGS?

28:27.840 --> 28:31.277
- HOW HARD COULD IT BE?

28:31.310 --> 28:32.344
- GO.

28:32.378 --> 28:35.281
- AHHHH!

28:47.126 --> 28:49.361
- COAST IS CLEAR.

28:49.395 --> 28:51.030
- THANKS, MOM.

28:51.063 --> 28:52.398
- KENDALL.

28:52.431 --> 28:55.167
- OH, BUCKET, BUCKET.
PUT THE BUCKET ON.

28:55.201 --> 28:57.369
- HONEY BUNNY.

28:57.403 --> 29:00.339
- HONEY, YOU HAVE GOT TO BE FIRM
WITH THIS GIRL.

29:00.372 --> 29:02.809
JUST TELL HER THAT YOU ARE
NEVER, EVER GOING TO DATE HER

29:02.842 --> 29:05.544
AND SHE SHOULD GO BACK
TO HER BOYFRIEND.

29:05.577 --> 29:10.149
- JUST GIVE ME SOME LEMONADE,
AND I'LL THINK ABOUT IT.

29:10.182 --> 29:12.151
[slurping]

29:12.184 --> 29:15.021
- OKAY,
BEFORE YOU SURRENDER YOURSELF

29:15.054 --> 29:16.956
TO A LIFE UNDER THE SEA,

29:16.989 --> 29:21.193
WE HAVE TO SEE
IF YOU CAN HANDLE IT.

29:21.227 --> 29:25.431
- YEAH, I CAN DO THIS.

29:25.464 --> 29:28.400
I THINK I LIKE HAVING A TAIL.

29:32.304 --> 29:35.407
- NOW, THERE'S NO CUDA MAN SPRAY
IN THE OCEAN,

29:35.441 --> 29:39.545
SO YOU'RE GOING TO HAVE TO
GET USED TO SMELLING LIKE FISH.

29:42.481 --> 29:44.016
WHOA, OH, IT'S HIDEOUS.

29:44.050 --> 29:45.852
OH, OH, OH.

29:45.885 --> 29:47.987
OHH, OHH, OHH.

29:48.020 --> 29:49.488
AHH!

29:49.521 --> 29:52.558
- NOW, MERMAIDS
DON'T EAT CHEESEBURGERS,

29:52.591 --> 29:57.096
SO ARE YOU PREPARED
TO GIVE UP THIS FOR THIS?

30:01.133 --> 30:03.970
MMM,
THAT'S GOOD SHELL.

30:04.003 --> 30:05.437
I COULD TOTALLY GIVE UP...

30:05.471 --> 30:07.473
PTHEW!

30:07.506 --> 30:09.175
OH, WHO AM I KIDDING?

30:09.208 --> 30:11.510
I LOVE CHEESEBURGERS
AND MAN SPRAY

30:11.543 --> 30:13.612
AND MY FEET.

30:13.645 --> 30:16.815
- THEN YOU'RE GONNA HAVE TO
TELL ANNIE IT'S OVER.

30:21.020 --> 30:23.522
- WE'RE JUST FROM
TWO DIFFERENT WORLDS.

30:27.426 --> 30:29.228
- YOU THINK HE'LL NOTICE?

30:29.261 --> 30:31.230
- WHO CARES?

30:31.263 --> 30:33.900
WE FOUND THE BURIED TREASURE.

30:37.069 --> 30:38.470
- TREASURE DANCE.

30:38.504 --> 30:40.306
[together]
OHH, WE'RE RICH.

30:40.339 --> 30:42.474
WE'RE RICH.
WE'RE RICH. WE'RE RICH.

30:42.508 --> 30:44.977
- OKAY, ALL RIGHT.

30:45.011 --> 30:48.981
STAND BACK AND PREPARE TO GAZE
UPON THE RICH TREASURE

30:49.015 --> 30:52.284
OF SCRATCHY THE PIRATE.

30:52.318 --> 30:55.087
UH...IT'S LOCKED.

30:55.121 --> 30:57.189
ALL RIGHT, BOYS, WE GAVE IT
A GOOD SHOT, DIDN'T WE?

30:57.223 --> 30:58.424
- WHOA, WHOA, WHOA, WHOA,
WHAT?

30:58.457 --> 30:59.425
WAIT, WAIT, WAIT, WAIT, WAIT.

30:59.458 --> 31:02.494
STAND BACK, BOYS,
BECAUSE CARLOS THE PIRATE

31:02.528 --> 31:06.298
HAS GOT THIS.

31:06.332 --> 31:07.499
BRING IT.

31:07.533 --> 31:12.171
YAAAA!

31:12.204 --> 31:13.572
[coughs]

31:13.605 --> 31:15.574
IT'S A TOUGH LOCK.

31:15.607 --> 31:17.243
- THERE'S GOT TO BE A WAY
TO OPEN THIS.

31:17.276 --> 31:21.280
EVERYBODY JUST THINK.

31:21.313 --> 31:23.449
- OH, OHH.

31:23.482 --> 31:25.084
OH, IT'S GOT ME.

31:25.117 --> 31:26.418
- KENDALL.

31:26.452 --> 31:29.321
- SANDY,
WE NEED TO TALK.

31:29.355 --> 31:34.326
- I KNOW, BECAUSE YOU CAN'T WAIT
TO WEAR OUR PROMISE RING.

31:34.360 --> 31:35.327
- OH, NO.

31:35.361 --> 31:37.196
- YO, KENDALL, JO CALLED.

31:37.229 --> 31:38.497
SHE'S LOOKING FOR YOU.

31:38.530 --> 31:41.433
SHE DOESN'T SOUND HAPPY.

31:41.467 --> 31:42.668
- PROMISE RINGS?

31:42.701 --> 31:45.404
- JO, THIS IS A LONG STORY,
BUT I CAN EXPLAIN EVERYTHING.

31:45.437 --> 31:46.472
SHE THREW THE PHONE AGAIN.

31:46.505 --> 31:51.077
- HEY.

31:51.110 --> 31:53.980
- SANDY,
I DON'T WANT THIS PROMISE RING.

31:54.013 --> 31:56.648
THERE'S NOTHING BETWEEN US,
AND THERE NEVER WILL BE.

31:56.682 --> 31:58.450
NOW, I'VE BEEN TRYING
TO BE NICE ALL DAY,

31:58.484 --> 32:02.221
AND IT'S NOT WORKING,
SO I NEED YOU TO LEAVE ME ALONE.

32:02.254 --> 32:04.190
- I UNDERSTAND.

32:04.223 --> 32:07.493
TAD!

32:07.526 --> 32:09.261
HE HURT MY FEELINGS.

32:09.295 --> 32:10.496
BEAT HIM UP.
- WHAT?

32:10.529 --> 32:13.432
- FIRST YOU STEAL MY GIRLFRIEND,
THEN YOU HURT HER FEELINGS?

32:13.465 --> 32:16.102
IT'S TAD GETS MAD TIME.

32:16.135 --> 32:18.404
- TWO CAN PLAY THIS GAME.

32:18.437 --> 32:19.405
GUYS.

32:19.438 --> 32:21.007
- HI, TEENS.

32:21.040 --> 32:22.108
- NOT WHAT I WAS GOING FOR.

32:22.141 --> 32:23.609
- I'VE BEEN GIVING THIS
SOME THOUGHT.

32:23.642 --> 32:28.414
THERE'S ONLY ONE WAY
TO SETTLE THIS, A DRAG RACE.

32:28.447 --> 32:30.516
- I CAN THINK OF, LIKE,
57 OTHER WAYS TO SETTLE THIS.

32:30.549 --> 32:32.451
- YEAH, IF KENDALL WINS,

32:32.484 --> 32:35.487
YOU TROUBLEMAKERS
WILL LEAVE THE BEACH FOREVER,

32:35.521 --> 32:39.191
BUT IF TAD WINS, KENDALL AND ALL
HIS HOLLYWOOD FRIENDS

32:39.225 --> 32:43.529
LEAVE THE BEACH
NEVER TO RETURN AGAIN.

32:43.562 --> 32:44.630
- WHAT?

32:44.663 --> 32:46.999
- SOUNDS LIKE SOMEONE
IS CHICKEN.

32:47.033 --> 32:48.200
- OHH.

32:48.234 --> 32:49.135
- CHECK IT OUT, EVERYONE.

32:49.168 --> 32:50.602
HOLLYWOOD IS CHICKEN,

32:50.636 --> 32:53.005
BECAUSE HE KNOWS
WHEN IT COME TO DRAG RACING

32:53.039 --> 32:57.076
AGAINST TAD,
HE'LL LOSE....BAD.

32:57.109 --> 32:59.078
[together]
DRAG RACE, DRAG RACE,

32:59.111 --> 33:01.447
DRAG RACE, DRAG RACE,
DRAG RACE, DRAG RACE.

33:01.480 --> 33:02.714
- YOU'RE ON.

33:02.748 --> 33:06.118
[together]
WHOO!

33:06.152 --> 33:07.353
- PERFECT.

33:07.386 --> 33:10.256
ALL WE HAVE TO DO IS MAKE SURE
KENDALL LOSES THE DRAG RACE.

33:10.289 --> 33:13.625
THAT WAY, BTR CAN NEVER
COME BACK TO THIS BEACH AGAIN.

33:13.659 --> 33:16.495
- OR WE COULD GET OFF
THIS DANGEROUS BLUFF

33:16.528 --> 33:18.497
AND JUST HAVE A FUN DAY
AT THE BEACH.

33:18.530 --> 33:19.798
IT'S A BEAUTIFUL DAY.

33:19.831 --> 33:21.700
- MY PLAN'S BETTER.

33:21.733 --> 33:23.435
HIGH FIVE.

33:23.469 --> 33:24.436
AHHH!

33:24.470 --> 33:27.439
[yelling]

33:33.179 --> 33:35.347
I HATE THE BEACH.

33:35.381 --> 33:38.350
[upbeat guitar surfer music]

33:38.384 --> 33:43.055
*

33:43.089 --> 33:46.425
- DRAG RACE IT IS,
ATVs, SYCAMORE BEACH,

33:46.458 --> 33:48.627
ONE HOUR,
BE THERE...

33:48.660 --> 33:51.597
ON YOUR ATV...
FOR THE DRAG...

33:51.630 --> 33:53.365
THAT WE'RE HAVING.

33:53.399 --> 33:57.569
DON'T FORGET.
- I GOT IT.

33:57.603 --> 34:02.108
- YOU MADE A BIG MISTAKE
FALLING IN LOVE WITH ME.

34:04.610 --> 34:05.611
- A DRAG RACE?

34:05.644 --> 34:08.280
- THAT'S THE WAY OF THE BEACH.

34:08.314 --> 34:09.781
I'LL LET YOU USE MY ATV.

34:09.815 --> 34:13.252
- YEAH ONE PROBLEM: I'VE NEVER
DRIVEN AT ATV IN MY LIFE.

34:13.285 --> 34:17.223
- THEN WHAT ARE YOU DOING
CHALLENGING TAD TO A DRAG RACE?

34:20.626 --> 34:22.494
- HA-HA, WHOO.

34:22.528 --> 34:24.096
- WHERE DID YOU GET A CANNON?

34:24.130 --> 34:26.298
- AT THE CANNON STORE.

34:26.332 --> 34:27.633
- LESS TALKIN',
MORE BLASTIN'.

34:27.666 --> 34:31.437
- [cackles]

34:31.470 --> 34:34.840
- OH-HO-HO-HO-HO.

34:34.873 --> 34:37.576
- WAIT A MINUTE.

34:37.609 --> 34:40.179
- HOW DID WE MISS THAT?

34:40.212 --> 34:41.213
- BLOW IT OUT.

34:41.247 --> 34:44.316
- AHH!

34:44.350 --> 34:45.417
- PUT IT OUT.

34:45.451 --> 34:46.418
[cannon booming]

34:46.452 --> 34:50.256
[car alarm blaring]

34:50.289 --> 34:53.625
- YEAH, WE MISSED.

34:53.659 --> 34:56.628
- THIS IS SO BAD.

34:56.662 --> 34:57.629
- I'LL SAY.

34:57.663 --> 35:01.500
THAT WAS OUR ONLY CANNONBALL.

35:01.533 --> 35:03.335
- YES.

35:03.369 --> 35:04.903
NO.

35:04.936 --> 35:07.306
YE--YOU SHOULD
BE WEARING GLOVES TO--

35:07.339 --> 35:10.276
MARVIN, THE PARTY STARTS
IN TWO HOURS' TIME.

35:10.309 --> 35:11.643
YOU PROMISED ME A ROCKING BAND.

35:11.677 --> 35:13.812
I'M SCANNING THE HORIZON,
AND THERE IS NO--

35:13.845 --> 35:15.447
WHAT DO YOU MEAN
THEY SHOULD BE HERE?

35:15.481 --> 35:18.450
[upbeat music]

35:18.484 --> 35:20.819
MARVIN, I'M NOT HAPPY.

35:20.852 --> 35:23.289
FELLAS, COULD YOU STOP
THOSE SOUNDS JUST FOR A MOMENT

35:23.322 --> 35:25.257
SO I CAN MAYBE THINK?

35:25.291 --> 35:27.326
OHH!

35:27.359 --> 35:29.828
- OKAY, I'VE READ AND REVIEWED
ALL THE SCRIPTS,

35:29.861 --> 35:33.465
AND I HAVE DECIDED
THAT YOU SHOULD DO THIS ONE.

35:33.499 --> 35:35.234
- FUMBLE BUMS.

35:35.267 --> 35:36.702
- THE FOOTBALL
BRIT-OUT-WATER STORY

35:36.735 --> 35:38.404
APPEALS TO YOUR CORE BASE,

35:38.437 --> 35:40.539
AND YOUR MONKEY SIDEKICK
MAKES IT FAMILY FRIENDLY,

35:40.572 --> 35:44.643
THUS GUARANTEE $100 MIL-PLUS
OPENING WEEKEND.

35:44.676 --> 35:47.513
- MONKEY SIDEKICK, HUH?

35:47.546 --> 35:49.448
PUT THIS ON THE "MAYBE" PILE.

35:49.481 --> 35:52.451
KATIE, I'M VERY IMPRESSED
WITH A LOT

35:52.484 --> 35:54.320
OF YOUR ACHIEVEMENTS TODAY,
BUT REALLY, STICKLY,

35:54.353 --> 35:57.223
I CAN'T HAVE A LITTLE,
TEN-YEAR-OLD MANAGER, CAN I?

35:57.256 --> 35:59.225
I'M A RESPECTABLE,
CREDIBLE MAN.

35:59.258 --> 36:01.593
- SIGN WITH MY MANAGEMENT
RIGHT NOW,

36:01.627 --> 36:03.429
AND I WILL HAVE A ROCKING BAND

36:03.462 --> 36:06.632
WITH AN INTERNATIONAL
NUMBER ONE HIT HERE IN AN HOUR.

36:06.665 --> 36:09.601
- LISTEN, KID,

36:09.635 --> 36:12.471
DON'T PLAY MIND GAMES WITH ME.

36:12.504 --> 36:14.540
PLUS, I'VE ALREADY GOT
A FANTASTIC,

36:14.573 --> 36:16.875
MORE THAN ADEQUATE BAND
HERE ALREADY.

36:16.908 --> 36:17.876
HIT IT, GUYS.

36:17.909 --> 36:19.911
[upbeat music]

36:19.945 --> 36:22.481
- OH-HO-HO,
LISTEN TO THAT.

36:22.514 --> 36:24.950
HOW CAN I BE DEFEATED?

36:24.983 --> 36:29.921
*

36:31.657 --> 36:33.659
- JUST BREAK IT TO HER GENTLY,

36:33.692 --> 36:36.628
AND DON'T GET CAUGHT UP
IN THE MOMENT AND KISS HER.

36:36.662 --> 36:38.797
I KNOW YOU DO THAT SOMETIMES.

36:38.830 --> 36:41.467
- NO PROBLEMO WITH MERMAIDO.

36:41.500 --> 36:43.602
- HEY.

36:43.635 --> 36:46.605
HEY, I WAS JUST ON MY WAY
TO THE BEACH HOUSE.

36:46.638 --> 36:48.474
- ANNIE, I'M SORRY.

36:48.507 --> 36:51.310
THERE CAN BE
NO MORE BEACH HOUSE FOR US

36:51.343 --> 36:54.713
OR BEACH OR EATING CLAMS
ON THE OCEAN FLOOR.

36:54.746 --> 36:56.014
- I DON'T UNDERSTAND.

36:56.047 --> 36:56.882
I THOUGHT THAT WE WERE...

36:56.915 --> 36:58.850
- SHH-SHH-SHH-SHH-SHH.
- DOING OKAY.

36:58.884 --> 37:00.819
- WE'RE FROM TWO
DIFFERENT WORLDS,

37:00.852 --> 37:02.554
BUT I'LL NEVER FORGET YOU.

37:02.588 --> 37:05.657
- I'M NOT REALLY SURE
WHAT THAT MEANS,

37:05.691 --> 37:08.327
BUT I'M HOPING THIS WILL CHANGE
YOUR MIND.

37:08.360 --> 37:09.661
- JAMES, NO!

37:09.695 --> 37:11.630
- AHH,
THE MERMAID'S KISS!

37:11.663 --> 37:14.266
OH,
THE TRANSFORMATION IS UPON ME.

37:14.300 --> 37:16.335
YEEE!

37:16.368 --> 37:17.436
[chirping]

37:17.469 --> 37:18.504
THIS BETTER WORK.

37:18.537 --> 37:21.507
[yelling and chirping]

37:25.577 --> 37:27.479
HOW LONG IS THIS GONNA TAKE,
EXACTLY?

37:27.513 --> 37:29.315
- YOU'RE NOT A MERMAID,
ARE YOU?

37:29.348 --> 37:30.949
- WHAT?
NO.

37:30.982 --> 37:32.484
- WHAT?

37:32.518 --> 37:35.487
NO, NO, YOU SAID YOU GREW UP
IN THE WATER.

37:35.521 --> 37:37.523
YOU ATE A CLAM SHELL AND ALL.

37:37.556 --> 37:41.660
AND YOU SAID YOU JUST TALKED
TO YOUR DAD AT THE OCEAN FLOOR.

37:41.693 --> 37:43.495
- YEAH,
I'VE BEEN A COMPETITIVE SWIMMER

37:43.529 --> 37:44.630
SINCE I WAS THREE.

37:44.663 --> 37:45.931
I ATE THE CLAM SHELL AND ALL,

37:45.964 --> 37:48.033
BECAUSE IT'S A TRICK
THAT MY DAD TAUGHT ME,

37:48.066 --> 37:50.502
WHO OWNS THE OCEAN FLOOR,

37:50.536 --> 37:53.572
THE RESTAURANT
RIGHT DOWN THE BEACH, YOU KNOW?

37:53.605 --> 37:55.507
- OHHHH.

37:55.541 --> 37:57.008
- YEAH.

37:57.042 --> 37:59.478
- SO COULD WE JUST PRETEND

37:59.511 --> 38:03.649
THESE LAST FEW MINUTES HERE
NEVER HAPPENED?

38:03.682 --> 38:06.485
- I THINK YOU'RE LUCKY
YOU'RE CUTE.

38:06.518 --> 38:11.490
- THAT'S A YES.

38:11.523 --> 38:14.059
- I'M GONNA BE COMING DOWN
TO THIS BEACH A LOT MORE OFTEN.

38:14.092 --> 38:17.696
- OHH, NOT IF KENDALL LOSES
THAT DRAG RACE YOU'RE NOT.

38:17.729 --> 38:19.097
LET'S GO.

38:19.130 --> 38:22.334
[all cheering]

38:22.368 --> 38:24.836
- MAN,
WE HAD NO LUCK TODAY.

38:24.870 --> 38:26.638
- WHICH IS WEIRD
CONSIDERING I'VE HAD

38:26.672 --> 38:29.341
ME LUCKY KEY WITH ME
THE WHOLE TIME.

38:29.375 --> 38:32.478
IT'S BEEN IN ME FAMILY
FOR GENERATIONS.

38:32.511 --> 38:33.512
- GIVE ME THAT.

38:33.545 --> 38:36.582
- OPEN IT. OPEN IT.
OPEN IT. OPEN IT. OPEN IT.

38:43.889 --> 38:45.691
all: WE'RE RICH!

38:45.724 --> 38:48.827
WE'RE RICH.
WE'RE RICH. WE'RE RICH.

38:48.860 --> 38:50.128
- I'M GONNA PREPAY
FOR MED SCHOOL.

38:50.161 --> 38:53.565
- I'M GONNA GET MY BEACH HOUSE
FOR THE JENNIFERS.

38:53.599 --> 38:56.735
- I'M GONNA BUY
ANOTHER CANNONBALL.

38:56.768 --> 38:58.604
- I'M GOING TO USE THIS TO PAY

38:58.637 --> 39:02.541
FOR MY PRICELESS MING VASE
COLLECTION AND MY SPORTS CAR.

39:05.076 --> 39:08.747
YOU DO REALIZE I HAVE
SURVEILLANCE CAMERAS EVERYWHERE.

39:08.780 --> 39:11.717
- OF COURSE, YOU DO.
- YEP.

39:14.953 --> 39:18.924
- OKAY,
I'M GONNA GO MAKE A SANDWICH.

39:18.957 --> 39:20.859
- WELL, BOYS,
WE DIDN'T GET THE TREASURE,

39:20.892 --> 39:23.128
BUT AT LEAST WE HAD
A ROUSING PIRATE ADVENTURE.

39:23.161 --> 39:24.563
- YEAH.
- YEAH, TRUE.

39:24.596 --> 39:26.465
- AND NEXT WEEK,
WE'RE GOING AFTER

39:26.498 --> 39:29.568
ME GREAT-GREAT GRANDPAPPY
SNUGGIE TREASURE.

39:29.601 --> 39:33.472
- OHH.
- OH, SWEET.

39:33.505 --> 39:36.141
- OH, NOT IF KENDALL LOSES
THAT DRAG RACE YOU WON'T.

39:36.174 --> 39:37.509
